{%- if kind == "summary" %}

### Summary shape for this source (content_type = {{ content_type }})

{%- if content_type == "paper" %}
- Narrative: contribution (1 sentence), method (1-2 sentences),
  primary results (1-2 sentences).
- Each key claim MUST cite a section, figure, or table
  (e.g. "§4.2", "Fig 3", "Table 1").
{%- elif content_type == "book" %}
- Narrative: thesis (1 sentence), structure (1 sentence), core
  argument (1-2 sentences).
- Each key claim MUST cite a chapter or part
  (e.g. "Ch 3", "Part II").
{%- elif content_type == "article" %}
- Narrative: central claim (1 sentence), supporting evidence
  (1-2 sentences), context (1 sentence).
- One key claim per distinct assertion; keep each claim
  self-contained.
{%- elif content_type == "lecture" or content_type == "talk" %}
- Narrative: speaker + venue if known, thesis (1 sentence),
  demonstrations / examples (1-2 sentences).
- Each key claim MUST include a [MM:SS] timestamp drawn from the
  transcript's existing anchors.
{%- elif content_type == "podcast" %}
- Narrative: host + guest if known, thesis (1 sentence), topics
  covered (1-2 sentences). Distinguish host framing from guest
  claims in the prose.
- Each key claim MUST include a [MM:SS] timestamp.
{%- elif content_type == "movie" %}
- Narrative: logline (1 sentence), synopsis (1-2 sentences, no
  spoilers unless the synopsis requires them — mark with a
  "[spoiler]" prefix if so).
- Each key claim is a theme, not a factual assertion; one theme
  per entry.
{%- elif content_type == "video" or content_type == "audio" %}
- Narrative: 1-2 sentences describing what the source covers.
- One key claim per distinct point made in the source.
{%- else %}
- Narrative: 1-2 paragraph summary.
- 3-5 self-contained key claims.
{%- endif %}

Run these commands from within the workdir. Body content for the
summary goes in a short text file; each key claim is an inline
string.

# Single call that creates summary.json:
{{ disk }} summary-emit --workdir {{ workdir }} \
    --summary-file <path to a file containing the 1-2 paragraph summary> \
    --claim "First key claim sentence." \
    --claim "Second key claim sentence." \
    ...
{%- elif kind == "sources" %}

First initialize the file, then append one source per call.

# Initialize once:
{{ disk }} sources-init --workdir {{ workdir }}

# Per source:
{{ disk }} source-add --workdir {{ workdir }} \
    --id src-1 --type paper \
    --title "<title>" \
    --mention-context "<one-line note on where in source it is cited>" \
    [--authors "Last, First" --authors "..." ]  \
    [--year 2021] [--arxiv 2106.09685] [--doi ...] [--isbn ...] \
    [--url ...]

Use type=paper | book | url | video. Ids must be unique within the
file and match ^src-\d+$.
{%- elif kind == "keywords" %}

First initialize the file, then append one item per call.

Write each proposed_body to `{{ workdir }}/bodies/<id>.body.md` and each
proposed_frontmatter to `{{ workdir }}/bodies/<id>.fm.yml` (YAML). For
extend actions, write the frontmatter delta to
`{{ workdir }}/bodies/<id>.fmdelta.yml`.

# Initialize once:
{{ disk }} items-init --workdir {{ workdir }} --kind keyword

# Create a new keyword:
{{ disk }} item-add --workdir {{ workdir }} --kind keyword \
    --id kw-1 --name "<name>" --action create \
    --rationale "<1-2 sentence rationale>" \
    --body-file {{ workdir }}/bodies/kw-1.body.md \
    --frontmatter-file {{ workdir }}/bodies/kw-1.fm.yml

# Extend an existing keyword:
{{ disk }} item-add --workdir {{ workdir }} --kind keyword \
    --id kw-2 --name "<existing name>" --action extend \
    --match-existing "12 KEYWORDS/<name>.md" \
    --rationale "..." \
    --body-file {{ workdir }}/bodies/kw-2.body.md \
    --proposed-section "<section title>" --proposed-mode append \
    [--frontmatter-delta-file {{ workdir }}/bodies/kw-2.fmdelta.yml]
{%- elif kind == "people" %}

